twitter.text: Which is what inspired https://t.co/lhkQ0mmMp8. Eduroam doesn't need to be complicated! https://t.co/hPySCFMPIs
Eduroam guide is now available on the WIki.  https://t.co/pBS6q5SgSu
The new "radius client" module lets you proxy the same packet to multiple home servers.  A feature requested since 1999!
A new "parallel" section lets you call multiple databases in parallel.
v4 can now call other virtual servers, to unlimited depth!  It also supports asynchronous child requests.
New website (https://t.co/XzySu1Gykm) now live!  Please let us known your opinions.  Does anything need changing? Can you find things?

As promised.  https://t.co/Go0DbAxou7

v4 now supports TACACS+ as an experimental protocol.
FreeRADIUS defines yet another RADIUS standard.  https://t.co/pwzHphCtyd
Big news next week.  No v4, but some major new functionality in the v4.0.x branch.
v4 update.  Tested master / worker thread exchanging fake packets.  1M req/reply per second per thread.  The new network IO is scalable.

I am using FreeRADIUS along with MySQL to authenticate users.

Users are saved in the radcheck table. User attributes are saved in the radreply table.

For example I have a user named Bob in the radcheck table.



Bob has a Session-Timeout value of 60 (1 minute) in the radreply table.



This all works fine. My problem is that RADIUS just re-authenticates Bob straight away. I assume this is because Bob still exists in the radcheck table.

Is there a way to remove Bob from the radcheck and radreply tables after the Session-Timeout time has been reached?
